An X Factor hopeful who wowed judges last night has told of her heartache after her step-brother drowned in a filthy swimming pool days after her audition.

Youth worker Monica Michael, 24, is struggling to cope with the death of Savvakis Georgiou, 18, who slipped and fell into a hotel pool in the Cypriot party town of Ayia Napa.

The promising footballer is reported to have been remained unseen at the bottom of the Kalypso Hotel pool for 20 minutes because the water was filled with condoms, syringes and cigarette butts.

