Ms Michael, from London, said: 'It's hard to believe that he was at my audition and now he is no longer here.

'Sav was a huge, huge fan of The X factor and he always wanted to see the show and how it was run and I was happy that he got to witness my audition before he died.

'It was really hard to watch the show on Saturday without him and I just hope that he is at peace in heaven.'

The singer said that her stepbrother had been on a boys' holiday to celebrate his recent signing to League Two football club Stevenage FC when he drowned in the pool on August 18.

